OL,3,CDangerous drugs stored incorrectly at
OL,4,Ccare home where man died, a court hears
OL,6,FShe has pleaded guilty to a second
OL,7,Fcharge that she wilfully neglected Mr
OL,8,FDavies between September 5 and
OL,9,FSeptember 9 that year by failing to
OL,10,Fdisclose she had wrongfully
OL,11,Fadministered morphine.
OL,13,FThe court heard that on the morning of
OL,14,FSeptember 6, Barnard erroneously gave
OL,15,Fhim Mr Dodsworth's medication. Having
OL,16,Fsoon realised her mistake, she
OL,17,Fdisposed of the drugs Mr Davies should
OL,18,Fhave received and pretended the
OL,19,Fmedication she did give him, intended
OL,20,Ffor Mr Dodsworth, had been dropped
OL,21,Fdown the sink.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
